It’s possible that Trump businesses could be eligible for other types of assistance under the bill’s provisions.
The Senate-approved bill prohibits Trump family hotels from getting coronavirus aid from a $500 billion fund that would be set up to help businesses that incurred losses from the coronavirus.
The following day, March 23, 2020, a post on Facebook claimed:"Donald Trump would receive $17 million for 3 hotels closed for 4 days under Republican bill!
Our rulingA Facebook post said, "Donald Trump would receive $17 million for three hotels closed for four days under Republican bill!
But no GOP bill contained language that would have given hotels owned by the Trump family $17 million.